Two taxi accidents left several people injured on Thursday morning.
ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall said in a statement that a woman, 44, had sustained moderate injuries after a taxi knocked her down next to Alpine road in Springfield.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
“At approximately 7am, paramedics arrived at the scene and found the woman lying next to the taxi.
She sustained moderate injuries to her hip and spine and was transported to Addington hospital for further medical care.”
